item.dc:creator: @pk_man_owned pk_man_owned
item.description:
@pk_man_owned wrote:

itai:

Fagex started fucking up and people didn’t like that shit so they made private servers, then fagex got butthurt. End of story.

The first server was Blood-Scape. Which was a Runescape Classic made in 2004. In late 2005 the first Runescape Private Server was made created it was then announced as a “474” server. In very early 2007 the first 317 server came. Which was the base of Delta. It was called “Flame Pkz.” As Runescape Private Server progressed 317 became more advanced and players started to get deep into coding 317 servers. 317 servers become more graphic in early 2008 and the bottom tabs became more advanced. 508’s came abouts in early 2009, 525 mid 2009, 574 in late 2009.

That should have helped you enough : )

You’re retarded.

With a name like Cocoa…I honestly wouldn’t care what you say.

mmk. You still don’t know shit about shit.

WL -> Blakescape -> something -> project 16[/quote]
